{
  "text": "In this section we present an improvement to ALG1 when m is xed. For m [CITATION_1] we show that can be slightly reduced without causing the algorithm to fail. In order to improve the performance also for m = 3; 4 we use an algorithm called ALG12 which is the intersection of ALG1 and ALG2 . For m = 2 we use a simple algorithm that has a 4=3 stretching factor.",
  "citation_candidates": [
